lead_paragraph: Search crews refocused their efforts today to look for bodies and wreckage, rather than survivors, where a military plane crashed off the Northern California coast on Friday. Only one survivor has been pulled from the Pacific Ocean, and two bodies have been recovered. Eight crewmen from the Air Force Reserve plane are missing.
abstract: Search crews refocus their efforts to look for bodies and wreckage, rather than survivors, where military plane crashed off Northern California coast; only one survivor, Tech Sgt Robert Vogel, has been rescued and two bodies recovered; eight members of crew are still missing; photo (M)

headline.main: Rescue Hopes Fade at Site of Military Plane Crash
